  "response": "Hult International Business School is generally considered a reputable private business school with several strengths:\n\nPros:\n1. Global campuses across multiple countries (Boston, London, Dubai, San Francisco, Shanghai)\n2. Strong focus on international business and entrepreneurship\n3. Offer MBA, undergraduate, and master's programs\n4. Accredited by international bodies like AACSB\n5. Diverse student body with students from many countries\n6. Emphasis on practical, experiential learning\n\nPotential Limitations:\n1. Higher tuition costs compared to some public universities\n2. Less traditional academic approach\n3. Not as highly ranked as top-tier business schools like Harvard or Stanford\n\nRankings:\n- Typically ranks in the top 50-100 business schools globally\n- QS World University Rankings often places it in the mid-tier range for business education\n\nOverall, Hult is considered a solid choice for students seeking an international business education, particularly those interested in a globally-oriented, practical learning environment. However, its reputation and value can vary depending on individual career goals and perspectives.\n\nProspective students should research thoroughly and compare it with other business schools to determine if it best fits their specific needs.",
